President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation on Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week, expressing gratitude to law enforcement officers and honoring those who have been killed or disabled in the line of duty. The administration is working to enhance the health and safety of law enforcement officers through initiatives such as funding for bulletproof vests, active shooter training, and mental health and wellness services. The President also highlights the importance of reducing violent crime and mentions the Project Safe Neighborhoods initiative, which has secured $50 million in funding. He calls on all Americans to observe Peace Officers Memorial Day and Police Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and encourages the flag to be flown at half-staff on Peace Officers Memorial Day. Melania and the President will light the White House in blue on May 15.